{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":2982770,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2021-12-21T17:40:52.154Z","cooked":"<p>I’m creating this post to draw extra attention to an upcoming breaking change to WPILib. The Drive classes, such as <code>DifferentialDrive</code>, no longer invert the right motor controller by default.</p>
<p>If you import your code from 2021 into the 2022 development environment, don’t forget to check your motor inversion. Most robots need the right side to be inverted or they will spin in circles instead of driving forward.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">rightMotorController.setInverted(true);
</code></pre>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2021-12-21T17:40:52.154Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":115,"reads":224,"readers_count":223,"score":709.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":398302,"topic_slug":"robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/arcade-drive-parameters-switched/403862/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Arcade drive parameters switched","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":6}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022/398302/1","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":6}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":6,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":2982772,"name":"Eli Barnett","username":"Oblarg","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/{size}/161674_2.png","created_at":"2021-12-21T17:43:30.448Z","cooked":"<p>Thank god; this took years to fix.  Teams should notice that there’s no need to change reversal standards between autonomous and teleoperated now.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2021-12-21T17:43:30.448Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":217,"readers_count":216,"score":253.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":398302,"topic_slug":"robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022","display_username":"Eli Barnett","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":13}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12381,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!"},"post_url":"/t/robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022/398302/2","custom_user_title":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":13}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":13,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":2983166,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2021-12-24T05:47:56.753Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Oblarg" data-post="2" data-topic="398302">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/48/161674_2.png" class="avatar"> Oblarg:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Teams should notice that there’s no need to change reversal standards between autonomous and teleoperated now.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>That’s an excellent point, and also requires a change to 2021 robot code. If you followed the WPILib Trajectory Tutorial to create your <code>DriveSubsystem</code> you will also need to update your inversion.</p>
<p>Before 2022, the tutorial was negating the <code>rightVolts</code> parameter.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  public void tankDriveVolts(double leftVolts, double rightVolts) {
    m_leftMotors.setVoltage(leftVolts);
    m_rightMotors.setVoltage(-rightVolts); // NEGATED in 2021
    m_drive.feed();
  }
</code></pre>
<p>Assuming you are now inverting the right motor(s), you should <em>not</em> negate the <code>rightVolts</code> parameter.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  public void tankDriveVolts(double leftVolts, double rightVolts) {
    m_leftMotors.setVoltage(leftVolts);
    m_rightMotors.setVoltage(rightVolts); // NOT NEGATED in 2022
    m_drive.feed();
  }
</code></pre>
<p>If you miss this step, your robot will drive correctly in teleop, but when driving a path/trajectory it will behave unpredictably, and most likely end up just spinning in a circle.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2021-12-24T05:47:56.753Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":145,"readers_count":144,"score":89.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":398302,"topic_slug":"robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022/398302/3","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3014958,"name":"Doug Hudson","username":"dougjoe2e","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/5fc32e/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-03-01T16:00:56.811Z","cooked":"<p>Your comment is interesting to me because (I’ve quadruple checked) we aren’t currently doing any motor controller inversion in our code (we used the Rev Hardware Client to set the config on the Sparx Max controllers on one side to invert) and both teleop and auto are using DifferentialDrive.ArcadeDrive… yet when commanded to move forward or backward (non-zero xSpeed, 0 zRotation) the Arcade drive in teleopPeriodic works correctly while in autonomousPeriodic, it spins.</p>
<p>Last year we used DifferentialDrive.ArcadeDrive for both modes (teleop/auto) as well and didn’t have to do any inversion between modes.  Did the WPILib fix for 2022 only apply to one of the modes?</p>
<p>(I think) it’ll be easy enough to work around what our team is seeing, but I was mostly just curious if anyone else has had this experience.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2022-03-01T16:00:56.811Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":15.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":398302,"topic_slug":"robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022","display_username":"Doug Hudson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":12381,"username":"Oblarg","name":"Eli Barnett","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/{size}/161674_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51636,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/robot-spinning-after-importing-to-2022/398302/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3014961,"name":"Eli Barnett","username":"Oblarg","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/{size}/161674_2.png","created_at":"2022-03-01T16:03:29.238Z","cooked":"<p>Well, what are you doing differently in autonomous and teleop?</p>
